<h1 class="cover-heading text-position-head">How to install</h1>

<div class="text-position-par1">
    <p class="lead">Python can be run on your terminal after downloading and installing it to your system. Note that there are currently two versions of Python: 2 and 3. Python 3 is preferred, as it is currently being updated and developed, while Python 2 is slowly being phased out.</p>
    
    <img src="/public/css/pic13.png" alt="Issue displaying image!">

    <p class="lead"><a href="https://www.python.org/downloads/" target="_blank" class="link_t"> Please click here</a> to install Python (version 3.7 or the latest version is ideal). You can test your installation with a simple "hello.py" file. In the file include the line "print("Hello, World!")" and use "python hello.py" in your terminal to execute the file.</p> 
    
    <img src="/public/css/pic19.png" alt="Issue displaying image!">
    <img src="/public/css/pic20.png" alt="Issue displaying image!">
    
    <p class="lead">Python is very well known for its large standard library that provide many portable and broad functionalities that are useful. Use of these libraries typically involves including a line at the top of your Python file like, "import module_name". You will also need to install the library on your system to use its methods. This can be done with the command, "pip install module_name" (PIP is a "Preferred Installer Program" that is included with your Python installation).</p>
    
